data.enText: a serious infectious disease in which swellings appear on the lungs and other parts of the body

tr: infection transmitted by inhalation or ingestion of tubercle bacilli and manifested in fever and small lesions (usually in the lungs but in various other parts of the body in acute stages)

value.def: Tuberculosis is a serious infectious disease that affects someone's lungs and other parts of their body. The abbreviation TB is also used.
value.tran: 肺结核;结核病(缩略形式为 TB)
